originalText.text: After failing to get an appointment at the other branches of Manhattan Wellness in the city because i had a Groupon ticket, i tried calling this branch. The staff was very helpful and nice and took the patience to work with me for a suitable appointment for my bf and i. When there everyone was super nice and friendly, the place is clean, and the cupping session was exquisite. The doctor was very attentive and knew what she was doing. a great cupping 1st time experience. I'm definitely going back for more cupping sessions and to try their chiropractor as well. Thanks!

originalText.text: I have been a previous customer and in fact have rated the other location. Coming to this location was convenient as it works best for transportation reasons. The office is completely renovated and very classy. This visit was beyond my highest expectations, i have always been against acupuncture but SOYOUNG the acupuncturist explained how it works and i felt comfortable to go with it. DR. T is an expert at his craft was able to see my shoulder and neck issues immediately and my medical massage by Danae was just magical for my issues. I want to thank everyone here including the smooth process in the front end. I will be back soon and will recommend

originalText.text: I have been going to Manhattan Wellness Group for about 6 months, and am generally there between 2 to 3x a week. I suffer from lower back pain that had an acute onset that left me debilitated. I spent weeks in pain, unable to walk, lie down, or sleep comfortably. I tried other places with little relief until luckily I happened upon this practice. The treatment I have received there has been life changing. I'm not sure what I would do without them. As someone who works in clinical research I can appreciate the difficulties that come with running a practice, and am often forgiving of the things we all get annoyed by when we see a doctor (wait times, insurance issues etc.). In the case of Manhattan Wellness no forgiveness has been necessary. I have been stunned by their professionalism, willingness to accommodate my last minute calls for same day appointments, and how much the staff have gone above and beyond for me on a regular basis. I rarely, if at all, have to wait to be seen (despite them having a busy practice). I have had a chance to meet many of the physical therapists, Chiropractors, massage therapists, and Acupuncturists associated with the practice but I would be remiss if I didn't specifically mention Dr Trabulsi, who has been a lifesaver these past few months. He always takes the time to listen to me, and to take extra time to treat me when he can see I'm in pain. Taylor, one of the massage therapists gives one of the best massages I have ever had. You can't go wrong with this place, they really take the time to treat the individual and provide treatment and support as holistically as possible.

originalText.text: I have been going to Manhattan wellness for a over a month and feel great! I started going because of sciatica pain that was so bad, I had a lot of trouble walking. Because of the combination of the different  therapies that are practiced there, I am almost pain free!! I love that I get to have some chiropractic work, Accupuncture, cupping, physical therapy and best of all a massage during each of my appointments there. This is without a doubt the best physical therapy practice I have ever had the pleasure to go to.

originalText.text: Honestly this is an amazing hidden gem in NYC! My mom, brother, and I have been going to the manhattan wellness group and we have always received the best treatment. This place is great for everyone in the family. The staff are amazing and genuinely care for providing the best treatments. We recommend this place to everyone. All the chiropractors are great and Dr. T is hilarious, you will be in good hands
